{"description_id":"PROSEDUR PENGOPERASIAN SEPARATOR BAHAN BAKAR
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Nyalakan power supply pada MCC di Ruang DG (MCC Load Center DG Room) dengan memposisikan knob ke (1).
2.	Nyalakan power supply pada LCP separator dengan memposisikan knob ke on
3.	Buka valve M0134 (separator 1) atau Valve M0132 (separator 2) dari tanki.
a.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0134.
b.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0132.
4.	Buka klep hisap Feed Pump.
5.	Saat power supply sudah masuk, separator pada posisi standby, tekan tombol start (warna hijau) pada LCP dan akan muncul pertanyaan “to start feed pump press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (feed pump akan menyala selama ± 525 detik)
6.	Saat timer sudah 0 detik, akan muncul pertanyaan lagi “to start separation press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (motor akan mulai berputar dan mulai mengajak separator untuk berputar bersama secara perlahan melalui friction pad selama ± 239 detik).
7.	Kemudian akan muncul pertanyaan “ to start separation press start button “, lalu tekan start lagi pada LCP, 3 way valve akan aktif dan separator akan mulai mendischarge / menyaring bahan bakar scr otomatis dengan mekanisme urutan sebagai berikut : 
a.	Cek P244 (SV 15) : open bowl - start discharge ( 10 detik ).
b.	Cek P232 (SV 15) : open bowl – discharge check, draining & return increase speed ( 15 detik )
c.	Cek P257 (SV 16) : closing bowl (15 detik ).
d.	Cek P233 (SV 10) : water seal ( 3 detik ).
e.	Cek P258 (V1) : 3 way valve aktif – BB mulai disaring dan setiap 60 menit, BB kotor dan lumpur yg sudah terpisah akan dikeluarkan oleh separator dengan membuka bowl-nya.
f.	Lalu P234 (SV 6) akan aktif untuk membuang sludge ke sludge/dirty oil tank (10 detik).
8.	Sistem akan berjalan secara otomatis diatur oleh PLC dan mengisi ke tanki harian BB
","description_en":"FUEL SEPARATOR OPERATING PROCEDURES
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Turn on the power supply to the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room) by positioning the knob to (1).
2.	Turn on the power supply to the LCP separator by positioning the knob to
3.	Open valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank.
a.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0134.
b.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0132.
4.	Open the feed pump suction valve.
5.	When the power supply is in, the separator is in the standby position. Press the start button (green) on the LCP, and the question "To start the feed pump, press the start button" will appear. Then press the start button (the feed pump will turn on for ± 525 seconds).
6.	When the timer reaches 0 seconds, another question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press the start button (the motor will start rotating and start inviting the separator to rotate together slowly via the friction pad for ± 239 seconds).
7.	Then the question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press start again on the LCP. The 3-way valve will be active, and the separator will start to discharge or filter fuel automatically with the following sequence mechanism:
a.	Check P244 (SV 15): open bowl; start discharge (10 seconds).
b.	Check P232 (SV 15): open bowl, discharge check, draining, and return increase speed (15 seconds)
c.	Check P257 (SV 16): closing bowl (15 seconds).
d.	Check P233 (SV 10): water seal (3 seconds).
e.	Check P258 (V1): A 3-way valve is active: BB starts to be filtered, and every 60 minutes, dirty BB and separated sludge will be removed by the separator by opening the bowl.
f.	Then P234 (SV 6) will be active to dump the sludge into the sludge/dirty oil tank (10 seconds).
8.	The system will run automatically, regulated by the PLC, and fill the daily BB tank.


B.	STOP SEPARATOR
1.	The sequence for turning off the separator is as follows:
a.	Check SV sludge is active (15 seconds)
b.	Stop the timer for 1737 seconds (at this time, the motor no longer rotates the separator, but the separator will continue to rotate until it stops).
2.	Close the Feed Pump suction valve by positioning the lever not in the direction of the pipe.
3.	Close valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank by positioning the valve to the right.
4.	Turn off the power supply on the LCP separator by positioning the knob toward off.
5.	Turn off the power supply at the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room). by positioning the knob at (0).
"}

4.	Open the feed pump suction valve.
5.	When the power supply is in, the separator is in the standby position. Press the start button (green) on the LCP, and the question "To start the feed pump, press the start button" will appear. Then press the start button (the feed pump will turn on for ± 525 seconds).
6.	When the timer reaches 0 seconds, another question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press the start button (the motor will start rotating and start inviting the separator to rotate together slowly via the friction pad for ± 239 seconds).
7.	Then the question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press start again on the LCP. The 3-way valve will be active, and the separator will start to discharge or filter fuel automatically with the following sequence mechanism:
a.	Check P244 (SV 15): open bowl; start discharge (10 seconds).
b.	Check P232 (SV 15): open bowl, discharge check, draining, and return increase speed (15 seconds)
c.	Check P257 (SV 16): closing bowl (15 seconds).
d.	Check P233 (SV 10): water seal (3 seconds).
e.	Check P258 (V1): A 3-way valve is active: BB starts to be filtered, and every 60 minutes, dirty BB and separated sludge will be removed by the separator by opening the bowl.
f.	Then P234 (SV 6) will be active to dump the sludge into the sludge/dirty oil tank (10 seconds).
8.	The system will run automatically, regulated by the PLC, and fill the daily BB tank.


B.	STOP SEPARATOR
1.	The sequence for turning off the separator is as follows:
a.	Check SV sludge is active (15 seconds)
b.	Stop the timer for 1737 seconds (at this time, the motor no longer rotates the separator, but the separator will continue to rotate until it stops).
2.	Close the Feed Pump suction valve by positioning the lever not in the direction of the pipe.
3.	Close valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank by positioning the valve to the right.
4.	Turn off the power supply on the LCP separator by positioning the knob toward off.
5.	Turn off the power supply at the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room). by positioning the knob at (0).
"}

description_json:
{"description_id":"PROSEDUR PENGOPERASIAN SEPARATOR BAHAN BAKAR
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Nyalakan power supply pada MCC di Ruang DG (MCC Load Center DG Room) dengan memposisikan knob ke (1).
2.	Nyalakan power supply pada LCP separator dengan memposisikan knob ke on
3.	Buka valve M0134 (separator 1) atau Valve M0132 (separator 2) dari tanki.
a.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0134.
b.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0132.
4.	Buka klep hisap Feed Pump.
5.	Saat power supply sudah masuk, separator pada posisi standby, tekan tombol start (warna hijau) pada LCP dan akan muncul pertanyaan “to start feed pump press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (feed pump akan menyala selama ± 525 detik)
6.	Saat timer sudah 0 detik, akan muncul pertanyaan lagi “to start separation press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (motor akan mulai berputar dan mulai mengajak separator untuk berputar bersama secara perlahan melalui friction pad selama ± 239 detik).
7.	Kemudian akan muncul pertanyaan “ to start separation press start button “, lalu tekan start lagi pada LCP, 3 way valve akan aktif dan separator akan mulai mendischarge / menyaring bahan bakar scr otomatis dengan mekanisme urutan sebagai berikut : 
a.	Cek P244 (SV 15) : open bowl - start discharge ( 10 detik ).
b.	Cek P232 (SV 15) : open bowl – discharge check, draining & return increase speed ( 15 detik )
c.	Cek P257 (SV 16) : closing bowl (15 detik ).
d.	Cek P233 (SV 10) : water seal ( 3 detik ).
e.	Cek P258 (V1) : 3 way valve aktif – BB mulai disaring dan setiap 60 menit, BB kotor dan lumpur yg sudah terpisah akan dikeluarkan oleh separator dengan membuka bowl-nya.
f.	Lalu P234 (SV 6) akan aktif untuk membuang sludge ke sludge/dirty oil tank (10 detik).
8.	Sistem akan berjalan secara otomatis diatur oleh PLC dan mengisi ke tanki harian BB
","description_en":"FUEL SEPARATOR OPERATING PROCEDURES
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Turn on the power supply to the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room) by positioning the knob to (1).
2.	Turn on the power supply to the LCP separator by positioning the knob to
3.	Open valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank.
a.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0134.
b.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0132.
4.	Open the feed pump suction valve.
5.	When the power supply is in, the separator is in the standby position. Press the start button (green) on the LCP, and the question "To start the feed pump, press the start button" will appear. Then press the start button (the feed pump will turn on for ± 525 seconds).
6.	When the timer reaches 0 seconds, another question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press the start button (the motor will start rotating and start inviting the separator to rotate together slowly via the friction pad for ± 239 seconds).
7.	Then the question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press start again on the LCP. The 3-way valve will be active, and the separator will start to discharge or filter fuel automatically with the following sequence mechanism:
a.	Check P244 (SV 15): open bowl; start discharge (10 seconds).
b.	Check P232 (SV 15): open bowl, discharge check, draining, and return increase speed (15 seconds)
c.	Check P257 (SV 16): closing bowl (15 seconds).
d.	Check P233 (SV 10): water seal (3 seconds).
e.	Check P258 (V1): A 3-way valve is active: BB starts to be filtered, and every 60 minutes, dirty BB and separated sludge will be removed by the separator by opening the bowl.
f.	Then P234 (SV 6) will be active to dump the sludge into the sludge/dirty oil tank (10 seconds).
8.	The system will run automatically, regulated by the PLC, and fill the daily BB tank.


B.	STOP SEPARATOR
1.	The sequence for turning off the separator is as follows:
a.	Check SV sludge is active (15 seconds)
b.	Stop the timer for 1737 seconds (at this time, the motor no longer rotates the separator, but the separator will continue to rotate until it stops).
2.	Close the Feed Pump suction valve by positioning the lever not in the direction of the pipe.
3.	Close valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank by positioning the valve to the right.
4.	Turn off the power supply on the LCP separator by positioning the knob toward off.
5.	Turn off the power supply at the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room). by positioning the knob at (0).
"}

{"description_id":"PROSEDUR PENGOPERASIAN SEPARATOR BAHAN BAKAR
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Nyalakan power supply pada MCC di Ruang DG (MCC Load Center DG Room) dengan memposisikan knob ke (1).
2.	Nyalakan power supply pada LCP separator dengan memposisikan knob ke on
3.	Buka valve M0134 (separator 1) atau Valve M0132 (separator 2) dari tanki.
a.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0134.
b.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0132.
4.	Buka klep hisap Feed Pump.
5.	Saat power supply sudah masuk, separator pada posisi standby, tekan tombol start (warna hijau) pada LCP dan akan muncul pertanyaan “to start feed pump press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (feed pump akan menyala selama ± 525 detik)
6.	Saat timer sudah 0 detik, akan muncul pertanyaan lagi “to start separation press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (motor akan mulai berputar dan mulai mengajak separator untuk berputar bersama secara perlahan melalui friction pad selama ± 239 detik).
7.	Kemudian akan muncul pertanyaan “ to start separation press start button “, lalu tekan start lagi pada LCP, 3 way valve akan aktif dan separator akan mulai mendischarge / menyaring bahan bakar scr otomatis dengan mekanisme urutan sebagai berikut : 
a.	Cek P244 (SV 15) : open bowl - start discharge ( 10 detik ).
b.	Cek P232 (SV 15) : open bowl – discharge check, draining & return increase speed ( 15 detik )
c.	Cek P257 (SV 16) : closing bowl (15 detik ).
d.	Cek P233 (SV 10) : water seal ( 3 detik ).
e.	Cek P258 (V1) : 3 way valve aktif – BB mulai disaring dan setiap 60 menit, BB kotor dan lumpur yg sudah terpisah akan dikeluarkan oleh separator dengan membuka bowl-nya.
f.	Lalu P234 (SV 6) akan aktif untuk membuang sludge ke sludge/dirty oil tank (10 detik).
8.	Sistem akan berjalan secara otomatis diatur oleh PLC dan mengisi ke tanki harian BB
","description_en":"FUEL SEPARATOR OPERATING PROCEDURES
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Turn on the power supply to the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room) by positioning the knob to (1).
2.	Turn on the power supply to the LCP separator by positioning the knob to
3.	Open valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank.
a.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0134.
b.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0132.
4.	Open the feed pump suction valve.
5.	When the power supply is in, the separator is in the standby position. Press the start button (green) on the LCP, and the question "To start the feed pump, press the start button" will appear. Then press the start button (the feed pump will turn on for ± 525 seconds).
6.	When the timer reaches 0 seconds, another question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press the start button (the motor will start rotating and start inviting the separator to rotate together slowly via the friction pad for ± 239 seconds).
7.	Then the question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press start again on the LCP. The 3-way valve will be active, and the separator will start to discharge or filter fuel automatically with the following sequence mechanism:
a.	Check P244 (SV 15): open bowl; start discharge (10 seconds).
b.	Check P232 (SV 15): open bowl, discharge check, draining, and return increase speed (15 seconds)
c.	Check P257 (SV 16): closing bowl (15 seconds).
d.	Check P233 (SV 10): water seal (3 seconds).
e.	Check P258 (V1): A 3-way valve is active: BB starts to be filtered, and every 60 minutes, dirty BB and separated sludge will be removed by the separator by opening the bowl.
f.	Then P234 (SV 6) will be active to dump the sludge into the sludge/dirty oil tank (10 seconds).
8.	The system will run automatically, regulated by the PLC, and fill the daily BB tank.


B.	STOP SEPARATOR
1.	The sequence for turning off the separator is as follows:
a.	Check SV sludge is active (15 seconds)
b.	Stop the timer for 1737 seconds (at this time, the motor no longer rotates the separator, but the separator will continue to rotate until it stops).
2.	Close the Feed Pump suction valve by positioning the lever not in the direction of the pipe.
3.	Close valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank by positioning the valve to the right.
4.	Turn off the power supply on the LCP separator by positioning the knob toward off.
5.	Turn off the power supply at the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room). by positioning the knob at (0).
"}

{"description_id":"PROSEDUR PENGOPERASIAN SEPARATOR BAHAN BAKAR
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Nyalakan power supply pada MCC di Ruang DG (MCC Load Center DG Room) dengan memposisikan knob ke (1).
2.	Nyalakan power supply pada LCP separator dengan memposisikan knob ke on
3.	Buka valve M0134 (separator 1) atau Valve M0132 (separator 2) dari tanki.
a.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0134.
b.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0132.
4.	Buka klep hisap Feed Pump.
5.	Saat power supply sudah masuk, separator pada posisi standby, tekan tombol start (warna hijau) pada LCP dan akan muncul pertanyaan “to start feed pump press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (feed pump akan menyala selama ± 525 detik)
6.	Saat timer sudah 0 detik, akan muncul pertanyaan lagi “to start separation press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (motor akan mulai berputar dan mulai mengajak separator untuk berputar bersama secara perlahan melalui friction pad selama ± 239 detik).
7.	Kemudian akan muncul pertanyaan “ to start separation press start button “, lalu tekan start lagi pada LCP, 3 way valve akan aktif dan separator akan mulai mendischarge / menyaring bahan bakar scr otomatis dengan mekanisme urutan sebagai berikut : 
a.	Cek P244 (SV 15) : open bowl - start discharge ( 10 detik ).
b.	Cek P232 (SV 15) : open bowl – discharge check, draining & return increase speed ( 15 detik )
c.	Cek P257 (SV 16) : closing bowl (15 detik ).
d.	Cek P233 (SV 10) : water seal ( 3 detik ).
e.	Cek P258 (V1) : 3 way valve aktif – BB mulai disaring dan setiap 60 menit, BB kotor dan lumpur yg sudah terpisah akan dikeluarkan oleh separator dengan membuka bowl-nya.
f.	Lalu P234 (SV 6) akan aktif untuk membuang sludge ke sludge/dirty oil tank (10 detik).
8.	Sistem akan berjalan secara otomatis diatur oleh PLC dan mengisi ke tanki harian BB
","description_en":"FUEL SEPARATOR OPERATING PROCEDURES
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Turn on the power supply to the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room) by positioning the knob to (1).
2.	Turn on the power supply to the LCP separator by positioning the knob to
3.	Open valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank.
a.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0134.
b.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0132.
4.	Open the feed pump suction valve.
5.	When the power supply is in, the separator is in the standby position. Press the start button (green) on the LCP, and the question "To start the feed pump, press the start button" will appear. Then press the start button (the feed pump will turn on for ± 525 seconds).
6.	When the timer reaches 0 seconds, another question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press the start button (the motor will start rotating and start inviting the separator to rotate together slowly via the friction pad for ± 239 seconds).
7.	Then the question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press start again on the LCP. The 3-way valve will be active, and the separator will start to discharge or filter fuel automatically with the following sequence mechanism:
a.	Check P244 (SV 15): open bowl; start discharge (10 seconds).
b.	Check P232 (SV 15): open bowl, discharge check, draining, and return increase speed (15 seconds)
c.	Check P257 (SV 16): closing bowl (15 seconds).
d.	Check P233 (SV 10): water seal (3 seconds).
e.	Check P258 (V1): A 3-way valve is active: BB starts to be filtered, and every 60 minutes, dirty BB and separated sludge will be removed by the separator by opening the bowl.
f.	Then P234 (SV 6) will be active to dump the sludge into the sludge/dirty oil tank (10 seconds).
8.	The system will run automatically, regulated by the PLC, and fill the daily BB tank.


B.	STOP SEPARATOR
1.	The sequence for turning off the separator is as follows:
a.	Check SV sludge is active (15 seconds)
b.	Stop the timer for 1737 seconds (at this time, the motor no longer rotates the separator, but the separator will continue to rotate until it stops).
2.	Close the Feed Pump suction valve by positioning the lever not in the direction of the pipe.
3.	Close valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank by positioning the valve to the right.
4.	Turn off the power supply on the LCP separator by positioning the knob toward off.
5.	Turn off the power supply at the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room). by positioning the knob at (0).
"}

{"description_id":"PROSEDUR PENGOPERASIAN SEPARATOR BAHAN BAKAR
A.	START SEPARATOR

3.	Buka valve M0134 (separator 1) atau Valve M0132 (separator 2) dari tanki.
a.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0134.
b.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0132.
4.	Buka klep hisap Feed Pump.
5.	Saat power supply sudah masuk, separator pada posisi standby, tekan tombol start (warna hijau) pada LCP dan akan muncul pertanyaan “to start feed pump press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (feed pump akan menyala selama ± 525 detik)
6.	Saat timer sudah 0 detik, akan muncul pertanyaan lagi “to start separation press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (motor akan mulai berputar dan mulai mengajak separator untuk berputar bersama secara perlahan melalui friction pad selama ± 239 detik).
7.	Kemudian akan muncul pertanyaan “ to start separation press start button “, lalu tekan start lagi pada LCP, 3 way valve akan aktif dan separator akan mulai mendischarge / menyaring bahan bakar scr otomatis dengan mekanisme urutan sebagai berikut : 
a.	Cek P244 (SV 15) : open bowl - start discharge ( 10 detik ).
b.	Cek P232 (SV 15) : open bowl – discharge check, draining & return increase speed ( 15 detik )
c.	Cek P257 (SV 16) : closing bowl (15 detik ).
d.	Cek P233 (SV 10) : water seal ( 3 detik ).
e.	Cek P258 (V1) : 3 way valve aktif – BB mulai disaring dan setiap 60 menit, BB kotor dan lumpur yg sudah terpisah akan dikeluarkan oleh separator dengan membuka bowl-nya.
f.	Lalu P234 (SV 6) akan aktif untuk membuang sludge ke sludge/dirty oil tank (10 detik).
8.	Sistem akan berjalan secara otomatis diatur oleh PLC dan mengisi ke tanki harian BB

{"description_id":"PROSEDUR PENGOPERASIAN SEPARATOR BAHAN BAKAR
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Nyalakan power supply pada MCC di Ruang DG (MCC Load Center DG Room) dengan memposisikan knob ke (1).
2.	Nyalakan power supply pada LCP separator dengan memposisikan knob ke on
3.	Buka valve M0134 (separator 1) atau Valve M0132 (separator 2) dari tanki.
a.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0134.
b.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0132.
4.	Buka klep hisap Feed Pump.
5.	Saat power supply sudah masuk, separator pada posisi standby, tekan tombol start (warna hijau) pada LCP dan akan muncul pertanyaan “to start feed pump press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (feed pump akan menyala selama ± 525 detik)
6.	Saat timer sudah 0 detik, akan muncul pertanyaan lagi “to start separation press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (motor akan mulai berputar dan mulai mengajak separator untuk berputar bersama secara perlahan melalui friction pad selama ± 239 detik).
7.	Kemudian akan muncul pertanyaan “ to start separation press start button “, lalu tekan start lagi pada LCP, 3 way valve akan aktif dan separator akan mulai mendischarge / menyaring bahan bakar scr otomatis dengan mekanisme urutan sebagai berikut : 
a.	Cek P244 (SV 15) : open bowl - start discharge ( 10 detik ).
b.	Cek P232 (SV 15) : open bowl – discharge check, draining & return increase speed ( 15 detik )
c.	Cek P257 (SV 16) : closing bowl (15 detik ).
d.	Cek P233 (SV 10) : water seal ( 3 detik ).
e.	Cek P258 (V1) : 3 way valve aktif – BB mulai disaring dan setiap 60 menit, BB kotor dan lumpur yg sudah terpisah akan dikeluarkan oleh separator dengan membuka bowl-nya.
f.	Lalu P234 (SV 6) akan aktif untuk membuang sludge ke sludge/dirty oil tank (10 detik).
8.	Sistem akan berjalan secara otomatis diatur oleh PLC dan mengisi ke tanki harian BB
","description_en":"FUEL SEPARATOR OPERATING PROCEDURES
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Turn on the power supply to the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room) by positioning the knob to (1).
2.	Turn on the power supply to the LCP separator by positioning the knob to
3.	Open valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank.
a.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0134.
b.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0132.
4.	Open the feed pump suction valve.
5.	When the power supply is in, the separator is in the standby position. Press the start button (green) on the LCP, and the question "To start the feed pump, press the start button" will appear. Then press the start button (the feed pump will turn on for ± 525 seconds).
6.	When the timer reaches 0 seconds, another question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press the start button (the motor will start rotating and start inviting the separator to rotate together slowly via the friction pad for ± 239 seconds).
7.	Then the question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press start again on the LCP. The 3-way valve will be active, and the separator will start to discharge or filter fuel automatically with the following sequence mechanism:
a.	Check P244 (SV 15): open bowl; start discharge (10 seconds).
b.	Check P232 (SV 15): open bowl, discharge check, draining, and return increase speed (15 seconds)
c.	Check P257 (SV 16): closing bowl (15 seconds).
d.	Check P233 (SV 10): water seal (3 seconds).
e.	Check P258 (V1): A 3-way valve is active: BB starts to be filtered, and every 60 minutes, dirty BB and separated sludge will be removed by the separator by opening the bowl.
f.	Then P234 (SV 6) will be active to dump the sludge into the sludge/dirty oil tank (10 seconds).
8.	The system will run automatically, regulated by the PLC, and fill the daily BB tank.


B.	STOP SEPARATOR
1.	The sequence for turning off the separator is as follows:
a.	Check SV sludge is active (15 seconds)
b.	Stop the timer for 1737 seconds (at this time, the motor no longer rotates the separator, but the separator will continue to rotate until it stops).
2.	Close the Feed Pump suction valve by positioning the lever not in the direction of the pipe.
3.	Close valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank by positioning the valve to the right.
4.	Turn off the power supply on the LCP separator by positioning the knob toward off.
5.	Turn off the power supply at the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room). by positioning the knob at (0).
"}

{"description_id":"PROSEDUR PENGOPERASIAN SEPARATOR BAHAN BAKAR
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Nyalakan power supply pada MCC di Ruang DG (MCC Load Center DG Room) dengan memposisikan knob ke (1).
2.	Nyalakan power supply pada LCP separator dengan memposisikan knob ke on
3.	Buka valve M0134 (separator 1) atau Valve M0132 (separator 2) dari tanki.
a.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0134.
b.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0132.
4.	Buka klep hisap Feed Pump.
5.	Saat power supply sudah masuk, separator pada posisi standby, tekan tombol start (warna hijau) pada LCP dan akan muncul pertanyaan “to start feed pump press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (feed pump akan menyala selama ± 525 detik)
6.	Saat timer sudah 0 detik, akan muncul pertanyaan lagi “to start separation press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (motor akan mulai berputar dan mulai mengajak separator untuk berputar bersama secara perlahan melalui friction pad selama ± 239 detik).
7.	Kemudian akan muncul pertanyaan “ to start separation press start button “, lalu tekan start lagi pada LCP, 3 way valve akan aktif dan separator akan mulai mendischarge / menyaring bahan bakar scr otomatis dengan mekanisme urutan sebagai berikut : 
a.	Cek P244 (SV 15) : open bowl - start discharge ( 10 detik ).
b.	Cek P232 (SV 15) : open bowl – discharge check, draining & return increase speed ( 15 detik )
c.	Cek P257 (SV 16) : closing bowl (15 detik ).
d.	Cek P233 (SV 10) : water seal ( 3 detik ).
e.	Cek P258 (V1) : 3 way valve aktif – BB mulai disaring dan setiap 60 menit, BB kotor dan lumpur yg sudah terpisah akan dikeluarkan oleh separator dengan membuka bowl-nya.
f.	Lalu P234 (SV 6) akan aktif untuk membuang sludge ke sludge/dirty oil tank (10 detik).
8.	Sistem akan berjalan secara otomatis diatur oleh PLC dan mengisi ke tanki harian BB
","description_en":"FUEL SEPARATOR OPERATING PROCEDURES
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Turn on the power supply to the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room) by positioning the knob to (1).
2.	Turn on the power supply to the LCP separator by positioning the knob to
3.	Open valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank.
a.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0134.
b.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0132.
4.	Open the feed pump suction valve.
5.	When the power supply is in, the separator is in the standby position. Press the start button (green) on the LCP, and the question "To start the feed pump, press the start button" will appear. Then press the start button (the feed pump will turn on for ± 525 seconds).
6.	When the timer reaches 0 seconds, another question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press the start button (the motor will start rotating and start inviting the separator to rotate together slowly via the friction pad for ± 239 seconds).
7.	Then the question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press start again on the LCP. The 3-way valve will be active, and the separator will start to discharge or filter fuel automatically with the following sequence mechanism:
a.	Check P244 (SV 15): open bowl; start discharge (10 seconds).
b.	Check P232 (SV 15): open bowl, discharge check, draining, and return increase speed (15 seconds)
c.	Check P257 (SV 16): closing bowl (15 seconds).
d.	Check P233 (SV 10): water seal (3 seconds).
e.	Check P258 (V1): A 3-way valve is active: BB starts to be filtered, and every 60 minutes, dirty BB and separated sludge will be removed by the separator by opening the bowl.
f.	Then P234 (SV 6) will be active to dump the sludge into the sludge/dirty oil tank (10 seconds).
8.	The system will run automatically, regulated by the PLC, and fill the daily BB tank.


B.	STOP SEPARATOR
1.	The sequence for turning off the separator is as follows:
a.	Check SV sludge is active (15 seconds)
b.	Stop the timer for 1737 seconds (at this time, the motor no longer rotates the separator, but the separator will continue to rotate until it stops).
2.	Close the Feed Pump suction valve by positioning the lever not in the direction of the pipe.
3.	Close valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank by positioning the valve to the right.
4.	Turn off the power supply on the LCP separator by positioning the knob toward off.
5.	Turn off the power supply at the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room). by positioning the knob at (0).
"}

{"description_id":"PROSEDUR PENGOPERASIAN SEPARATOR BAHAN BAKAR
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Nyalakan power supply pada MCC di Ruang DG (MCC Load Center DG Room) dengan memposisikan knob ke (1).
2.	Nyalakan power supply pada LCP separator dengan memposisikan knob ke on
3.	Buka valve M0134 (separator 1) atau Valve M0132 (separator 2) dari tanki.
a.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0134.
b.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0132.
4.	Buka klep hisap Feed Pump.
5.	Saat power supply sudah masuk, separator pada posisi standby, tekan tombol start (warna hijau) pada LCP dan akan muncul pertanyaan “to start feed pump press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (feed pump akan menyala selama ± 525 detik)
6.	Saat timer sudah 0 detik, akan muncul pertanyaan lagi “to start separation press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (motor akan mulai berputar dan mulai mengajak separator untuk berputar bersama secara perlahan melalui friction pad selama ± 239 detik).
7.	Kemudian akan muncul pertanyaan “ to start separation press start button “, lalu tekan start lagi pada LCP, 3 way valve akan aktif dan separator akan mulai mendischarge / menyaring bahan bakar scr otomatis dengan mekanisme urutan sebagai berikut : 
a.	Cek P244 (SV 15) : open bowl - start discharge ( 10 detik ).
b.	Cek P232 (SV 15) : open bowl – discharge check, draining & return increase speed ( 15 detik )
c.	Cek P257 (SV 16) : closing bowl (15 detik ).
d.	Cek P233 (SV 10) : water seal ( 3 detik ).
e.	Cek P258 (V1) : 3 way valve aktif – BB mulai disaring dan setiap 60 menit, BB kotor dan lumpur yg sudah terpisah akan dikeluarkan oleh separator dengan membuka bowl-nya.
f.	Lalu P234 (SV 6) akan aktif untuk membuang sludge ke sludge/dirty oil tank (10 detik).
8.	Sistem akan berjalan secara otomatis diatur oleh PLC dan mengisi ke tanki harian BB
","description_en":"FUEL SEPARATOR OPERATING PROCEDURES
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Turn on the power supply to the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room) by positioning the knob to (1).
2.	Turn on the power supply to the LCP separator by positioning the knob to
3.	Open valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank.
a.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0134.
b.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0132.
4.	Open the feed pump suction valve.
5.	When the power supply is in, the separator is in the standby position. Press the start button (green) on the LCP, and the question "To start the feed pump, press the start button" will appear. Then press the start button (the feed pump will turn on for ± 525 seconds).
6.	When the timer reaches 0 seconds, another question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press the start button (the motor will start rotating and start inviting the separator to rotate together slowly via the friction pad for ± 239 seconds).
7.	Then the question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press start again on the LCP. The 3-way valve will be active, and the separator will start to discharge or filter fuel automatically with the following sequence mechanism:
a.	Check P244 (SV 15): open bowl; start discharge (10 seconds).
b.	Check P232 (SV 15): open bowl, discharge check, draining, and return increase speed (15 seconds)
c.	Check P257 (SV 16): closing bowl (15 seconds).
d.	Check P233 (SV 10): water seal (3 seconds).
e.	Check P258 (V1): A 3-way valve is active: BB starts to be filtered, and every 60 minutes, dirty BB and separated sludge will be removed by the separator by opening the bowl.
f.	Then P234 (SV 6) will be active to dump the sludge into the sludge/dirty oil tank (10 seconds).
8.	The system will run automatically, regulated by the PLC, and fill the daily BB tank.


B.	STOP SEPARATOR
1.	The sequence for turning off the separator is as follows:
a.	Check SV sludge is active (15 seconds)
b.	Stop the timer for 1737 seconds (at this time, the motor no longer rotates the separator, but the separator will continue to rotate until it stops).
2.	Close the Feed Pump suction valve by positioning the lever not in the direction of the pipe.
3.	Close valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank by positioning the valve to the right.
4.	Turn off the power supply on the LCP separator by positioning the knob toward off.
5.	Turn off the power supply at the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room). by positioning the knob at (0).
"}

{"description_id":"PROSEDUR PENGOPERASIAN SEPARATOR BAHAN BAKAR
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Nyalakan power supply pada MCC di Ruang DG (MCC Load Center DG Room) dengan memposisikan knob ke (1).
2.	Nyalakan power supply pada LCP separator dengan memposisikan knob ke on
3.	Buka valve M0134 (separator 1) atau Valve M0132 (separator 2) dari tanki.
a.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0134.
b.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0132.
4.	Buka klep hisap Feed Pump.
5.	Saat power supply sudah masuk, separator pada posisi standby, tekan tombol start (warna hijau) pada LCP dan akan muncul pertanyaan “to start feed pump press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (feed pump akan menyala selama ± 525 detik)
6.	Saat timer sudah 0 detik, akan muncul pertanyaan lagi “to start separation press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (motor akan mulai berputar dan mulai mengajak separator untuk berputar bersama secara perlahan melalui friction pad selama ± 239 detik).
7.	Kemudian akan muncul pertanyaan “ to start separation press start button “, lalu tekan start lagi pada LCP, 3 way valve akan aktif dan separator akan mulai mendischarge / menyaring bahan bakar scr otomatis dengan mekanisme urutan sebagai berikut : 
a.	Cek P244 (SV 15) : open bowl - start discharge ( 10 detik ).
b.	Cek P232 (SV 15) : open bowl – discharge check, draining & return increase speed ( 15 detik )
c.	Cek P257 (SV 16) : closing bowl (15 detik ).
d.	Cek P233 (SV 10) : water seal ( 3 detik ).
e.	Cek P258 (V1) : 3 way valve aktif – BB mulai disaring dan setiap 60 menit, BB kotor dan lumpur yg sudah terpisah akan dikeluarkan oleh separator dengan membuka bowl-nya.
f.	Lalu P234 (SV 6) akan aktif untuk membuang sludge ke sludge/dirty oil tank (10 detik).
8.	Sistem akan berjalan secara otomatis diatur oleh PLC dan mengisi ke tanki harian BB
","description_en":"FUEL SEPARATOR OPERATING PROCEDURES
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Turn on the power supply to the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room) by positioning the knob to (1).
2.	Turn on the power supply to the LCP separator by positioning the knob to
3.	Open valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank.
a.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0134.
b.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0132.
4.	Open the feed pump suction valve.
5.	When the power supply is in, the separator is in the standby position. Press the start button (green) on the LCP, and the question "To start the feed pump, press the start button" will appear. Then press the start button (the feed pump will turn on for ± 525 seconds).
6.	When the timer reaches 0 seconds, another question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press the start button (the motor will start rotating and start inviting the separator to rotate together slowly via the friction pad for ± 239 seconds).
7.	Then the question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press start again on the LCP. The 3-way valve will be active, and the separator will start to discharge or filter fuel automatically with the following sequence mechanism:
a.	Check P244 (SV 15): open bowl; start discharge (10 seconds).
b.	Check P232 (SV 15): open bowl, discharge check, draining, and return increase speed (15 seconds)
c.	Check P257 (SV 16): closing bowl (15 seconds).
d.	Check P233 (SV 10): water seal (3 seconds).
e.	Check P258 (V1): A 3-way valve is active: BB starts to be filtered, and every 60 minutes, dirty BB and separated sludge will be removed by the separator by opening the bowl.
f.	Then P234 (SV 6) will be active to dump the sludge into the sludge/dirty oil tank (10 seconds).
8.	The system will run automatically, regulated by the PLC, and fill the daily BB tank.


B.	STOP SEPARATOR
1.	The sequence for turning off the separator is as follows:
a.	Check SV sludge is active (15 seconds)
b.	Stop the timer for 1737 seconds (at this time, the motor no longer rotates the separator, but the separator will continue to rotate until it stops).
2.	Close the Feed Pump suction valve by positioning the lever not in the direction of the pipe.
3.	Close valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank by positioning the valve to the right.
4.	Turn off the power supply on the LCP separator by positioning the knob toward off.
5.	Turn off the power supply at the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room). by positioning the knob at (0).
"}

{"description_id":"PROSEDUR PENGOPERASIAN SEPARATOR BAHAN BAKAR
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Nyalakan power supply pada MCC di Ruang DG (MCC Load Center DG Room) dengan memposisikan knob ke (1).
2.	Nyalakan power supply pada LCP separator dengan memposisikan knob ke on
3.	Buka valve M0134 (separator 1) atau Valve M0132 (separator 2) dari tanki.
a.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0134.
b.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0132.
4.	Buka klep hisap Feed Pump.
5.	Saat power supply sudah masuk, separator pada posisi standby, tekan tombol start (warna hijau) pada LCP dan akan muncul pertanyaan “to start feed pump press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (feed pump akan menyala selama ± 525 detik)
6.	Saat timer sudah 0 detik, akan muncul pertanyaan lagi “to start separation press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (motor akan mulai berputar dan mulai mengajak separator untuk berputar bersama secara perlahan melalui friction pad selama ± 239 detik).
7.	Kemudian akan muncul pertanyaan “ to start separation press start button “, lalu tekan start lagi pada LCP, 3 way valve akan aktif dan separator akan mulai mendischarge / menyaring bahan bakar scr otomatis dengan mekanisme urutan sebagai berikut : 
a.	Cek P244 (SV 15) : open bowl - start discharge ( 10 detik ).
b.	Cek P232 (SV 15) : open bowl – discharge check, draining & return increase speed ( 15 detik )
c.	Cek P257 (SV 16) : closing bowl (15 detik ).
d.	Cek P233 (SV 10) : water seal ( 3 detik ).
e.	Cek P258 (V1) : 3 way valve aktif – BB mulai disaring dan setiap 60 menit, BB kotor dan lumpur yg sudah terpisah akan dikeluarkan oleh separator dengan membuka bowl-nya.
f.	Lalu P234 (SV 6) akan aktif untuk membuang sludge ke sludge/dirty oil tank (10 detik).
8.	Sistem akan berjalan secara otomatis diatur oleh PLC dan mengisi ke tanki harian BB
","description_en":"FUEL SEPARATOR OPERATING PROCEDURES
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Turn on the power supply to the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room) by positioning the knob to (1).
2.	Turn on the power supply to the LCP separator by positioning the knob to
3.	Open valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank.
a.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0134.
b.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0132.
4.	Open the feed pump suction valve.
5.	When the power supply is in, the separator is in the standby position. Press the start button (green) on the LCP, and the question "To start the feed pump, press the start button" will appear. Then press the start button (the feed pump will turn on for ± 525 seconds).
6.	When the timer reaches 0 seconds, another question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press the start button (the motor will start rotating and start inviting the separator to rotate together slowly via the friction pad for ± 239 seconds).
7.	Then the question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press start again on the LCP. The 3-way valve will be active, and the separator will start to discharge or filter fuel automatically with the following sequence mechanism:
a.	Check P244 (SV 15): open bowl; start discharge (10 seconds).
b.	Check P232 (SV 15): open bowl, discharge check, draining, and return increase speed (15 seconds)
c.	Check P257 (SV 16): closing bowl (15 seconds).
d.	Check P233 (SV 10): water seal (3 seconds).
e.	Check P258 (V1): A 3-way valve is active: BB starts to be filtered, and every 60 minutes, dirty BB and separated sludge will be removed by the separator by opening the bowl.
f.	Then P234 (SV 6) will be active to dump the sludge into the sludge/dirty oil tank (10 seconds).
8.	The system will run automatically, regulated by the PLC, and fill the daily BB tank.


B.	STOP SEPARATOR
1.	The sequence for turning off the separator is as follows:
a.	Check SV sludge is active (15 seconds)
b.	Stop the timer for 1737 seconds (at this time, the motor no longer rotates the separator, but the separator will continue to rotate until it stops).
2.	Close the Feed Pump suction valve by positioning the lever not in the direction of the pipe.
3.	Close valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank by positioning the valve to the right.
4.	Turn off the power supply on the LCP separator by positioning the knob toward off.
5.	Turn off the power supply at the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room). by positioning the knob at (0).
"}

{"description_id":"PROSEDUR PENGOPERASIAN SEPARATOR BAHAN BAKAR
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Nyalakan power supply pada MCC di Ruang DG (MCC Load Center DG Room) dengan memposisikan knob ke (1).
2.	Nyalakan power supply pada LCP separator dengan memposisikan knob ke on
3.	Buka valve M0134 (separator 1) atau Valve M0132 (separator 2) dari tanki.
a.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0134.
b.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0132.
4.	Buka klep hisap Feed Pump.
5.	Saat power supply sudah masuk, separator pada posisi standby, tekan tombol start (warna hijau) pada LCP dan akan muncul pertanyaan “to start feed pump press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (feed pump akan menyala selama ± 525 detik)
6.	Saat timer sudah 0 detik, akan muncul pertanyaan lagi “to start separation press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (motor akan mulai berputar dan mulai mengajak separator untuk berputar bersama secara perlahan melalui friction pad selama ± 239 detik).
7.	Kemudian akan muncul pertanyaan “ to start separation press start button “, lalu tekan start lagi pada LCP, 3 way valve akan aktif dan separator akan mulai mendischarge / menyaring bahan bakar scr otomatis dengan mekanisme urutan sebagai berikut : 
a.	Cek P244 (SV 15) : open bowl - start discharge ( 10 detik ).
b.	Cek P232 (SV 15) : open bowl – discharge check, draining & return increase speed ( 15 detik )
c.	Cek P257 (SV 16) : closing bowl (15 detik ).
d.	Cek P233 (SV 10) : water seal ( 3 detik ).
e.	Cek P258 (V1) : 3 way valve aktif – BB mulai disaring dan setiap 60 menit, BB kotor dan lumpur yg sudah terpisah akan dikeluarkan oleh separator dengan membuka bowl-nya.
f.	Lalu P234 (SV 6) akan aktif untuk membuang sludge ke sludge/dirty oil tank (10 detik).
8.	Sistem akan berjalan secara otomatis diatur oleh PLC dan mengisi ke tanki harian BB
","description_en":"FUEL SEPARATOR OPERATING PROCEDURES
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Turn on the power supply to the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room) by positioning the knob to (1).
2.	Turn on the power supply to the LCP separator by positioning the knob to
3.	Open valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank.
a.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0134.
b.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0132.
4.	Open the feed pump suction valve.
5.	When the power supply is in, the separator is in the standby position. Press the start button (green) on the LCP, and the question "To start the feed pump, press the start button" will appear. Then press the start button (the feed pump will turn on for ± 525 seconds).
6.	When the timer reaches 0 seconds, another question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press the start button (the motor will start rotating and start inviting the separator to rotate together slowly via the friction pad for ± 239 seconds).
7.	Then the question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press start again on the LCP. The 3-way valve will be active, and the separator will start to discharge or filter fuel automatically with the following sequence mechanism:
a.	Check P244 (SV 15): open bowl; start discharge (10 seconds).
b.	Check P232 (SV 15): open bowl, discharge check, draining, and return increase speed (15 seconds)
c.	Check P257 (SV 16): closing bowl (15 seconds).
d.	Check P233 (SV 10): water seal (3 seconds).
e.	Check P258 (V1): A 3-way valve is active: BB starts to be filtered, and every 60 minutes, dirty BB and separated sludge will be removed by the separator by opening the bowl.
f.	Then P234 (SV 6) will be active to dump the sludge into the sludge/dirty oil tank (10 seconds).
8.	The system will run automatically, regulated by the PLC, and fill the daily BB tank.


B.	STOP SEPARATOR
1.	The sequence for turning off the separator is as follows:
a.	Check SV sludge is active (15 seconds)
b.	Stop the timer for 1737 seconds (at this time, the motor no longer rotates the separator, but the separator will continue to rotate until it stops).
2.	Close the Feed Pump suction valve by positioning the lever not in the direction of the pipe.
3.	Close valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank by positioning the valve to the right.
4.	Turn off the power supply on the LCP separator by positioning the knob toward off.
5.	Turn off the power supply at the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room). by positioning the knob at (0).
"}

{"description_id":"PROSEDUR PENGOPERASIAN SEPARATOR BAHAN BAKAR
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Nyalakan power supply pada MCC di Ruang DG (MCC Load Center DG Room) dengan memposisikan knob ke (1).
2.	Nyalakan power supply pada LCP separator dengan memposisikan knob ke on
3.	Buka valve M0134 (separator 1) atau Valve M0132 (separator 2) dari tanki.
a.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0134.
b.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0132.
4.	Buka klep hisap Feed Pump.
5.	Saat power supply sudah masuk, separator pada posisi standby, tekan tombol start (warna hijau) pada LCP dan akan muncul pertanyaan “to start feed pump press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (feed pump akan menyala selama ± 525 detik)
6.	Saat timer sudah 0 detik, akan muncul pertanyaan lagi “to start separation press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (motor akan mulai berputar dan mulai mengajak separator untuk berputar bersama secara perlahan melalui friction pad selama ± 239 detik).
7.	Kemudian akan muncul pertanyaan “ to start separation press start button “, lalu tekan start lagi pada LCP, 3 way valve akan aktif dan separator akan mulai mendischarge / menyaring bahan bakar scr otomatis dengan mekanisme urutan sebagai berikut : 
a.	Cek P244 (SV 15) : open bowl - start discharge ( 10 detik ).
b.	Cek P232 (SV 15) : open bowl – discharge check, draining & return increase speed ( 15 detik )
c.	Cek P257 (SV 16) : closing bowl (15 detik ).
d.	Cek P233 (SV 10) : water seal ( 3 detik ).
e.	Cek P258 (V1) : 3 way valve aktif – BB mulai disaring dan setiap 60 menit, BB kotor dan lumpur yg sudah terpisah akan dikeluarkan oleh separator dengan membuka bowl-nya.
f.	Lalu P234 (SV 6) akan aktif untuk membuang sludge ke sludge/dirty oil tank (10 detik).
8.	Sistem akan berjalan secara otomatis diatur oleh PLC dan mengisi ke tanki harian BB
","description_en":"FUEL SEPARATOR OPERATING PROCEDURES
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Turn on the power supply to the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room) by positioning the knob to (1).
2.	Turn on the power supply to the LCP separator by positioning the knob to
3.	Open valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank.
a.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0134.
b.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0132.
4.	Open the feed pump suction valve.
5.	When the power supply is in, the separator is in the standby position. Press the start button (green) on the LCP, and the question "To start the feed pump, press the start button" will appear. Then press the start button (the feed pump will turn on for ± 525 seconds).
6.	When the timer reaches 0 seconds, another question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press the start button (the motor will start rotating and start inviting the separator to rotate together slowly via the friction pad for ± 239 seconds).
7.	Then the question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press start again on the LCP. The 3-way valve will be active, and the separator will start to discharge or filter fuel automatically with the following sequence mechanism:
a.	Check P244 (SV 15): open bowl; start discharge (10 seconds).
b.	Check P232 (SV 15): open bowl, discharge check, draining, and return increase speed (15 seconds)
c.	Check P257 (SV 16): closing bowl (15 seconds).
d.	Check P233 (SV 10): water seal (3 seconds).
e.	Check P258 (V1): A 3-way valve is active: BB starts to be filtered, and every 60 minutes, dirty BB and separated sludge will be removed by the separator by opening the bowl.
f.	Then P234 (SV 6) will be active to dump the sludge into the sludge/dirty oil tank (10 seconds).
8.	The system will run automatically, regulated by the PLC, and fill the daily BB tank.


B.	STOP SEPARATOR
1.	The sequence for turning off the separator is as follows:
a.	Check SV sludge is active (15 seconds)
b.	Stop the timer for 1737 seconds (at this time, the motor no longer rotates the separator, but the separator will continue to rotate until it stops).
2.	Close the Feed Pump suction valve by positioning the lever not in the direction of the pipe.
3.	Close valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank by positioning the valve to the right.
4.	Turn off the power supply on the LCP separator by positioning the knob toward off.
5.	Turn off the power supply at the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room). by positioning the knob at (0).
"}

{"description_id":"PROSEDUR PENGOPERASIAN SEPARATOR BAHAN BAKAR
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Nyalakan power supply pada MCC di Ruang DG (MCC Load Center DG Room) dengan memposisikan knob ke (1).
2.	Nyalakan power supply pada LCP separator dengan memposisikan knob ke on
3.	Buka valve M0134 (separator 1) atau Valve M0132 (separator 2) dari tanki.
a.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0134.
b.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0132.
4.	Buka klep hisap Feed Pump.
5.	Saat power supply sudah masuk, separator pada posisi standby, tekan tombol start (warna hijau) pada LCP dan akan muncul pertanyaan “to start feed pump press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (feed pump akan menyala selama ± 525 detik)
6.	Saat timer sudah 0 detik, akan muncul pertanyaan lagi “to start separation press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (motor akan mulai berputar dan mulai mengajak separator untuk berputar bersama secara perlahan melalui friction pad selama ± 239 detik).
7.	Kemudian akan muncul pertanyaan “ to start separation press start button “, lalu tekan start lagi pada LCP, 3 way valve akan aktif dan separator akan mulai mendischarge / menyaring bahan bakar scr otomatis dengan mekanisme urutan sebagai berikut : 
a.	Cek P244 (SV 15) : open bowl - start discharge ( 10 detik ).
b.	Cek P232 (SV 15) : open bowl – discharge check, draining & return increase speed ( 15 detik )
c.	Cek P257 (SV 16) : closing bowl (15 detik ).
d.	Cek P233 (SV 10) : water seal ( 3 detik ).
e.	Cek P258 (V1) : 3 way valve aktif – BB mulai disaring dan setiap 60 menit, BB kotor dan lumpur yg sudah terpisah akan dikeluarkan oleh separator dengan membuka bowl-nya.
f.	Lalu P234 (SV 6) akan aktif untuk membuang sludge ke sludge/dirty oil tank (10 detik).
8.	Sistem akan berjalan secara otomatis diatur oleh PLC dan mengisi ke tanki harian BB
","description_en":"FUEL SEPARATOR OPERATING PROCEDURES
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Turn on the power supply to the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room) by positioning the knob to (1).
2.	Turn on the power supply to the LCP separator by positioning the knob to
3.	Open valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank.
a.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0134.
b.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0132.
4.	Open the feed pump suction valve.
5.	When the power supply is in, the separator is in the standby position. Press the start button (green) on the LCP, and the question "To start the feed pump, press the start button" will appear. Then press the start button (the feed pump will turn on for ± 525 seconds).
6.	When the timer reaches 0 seconds, another question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press the start button (the motor will start rotating and start inviting the separator to rotate together slowly via the friction pad for ± 239 seconds).
7.	Then the question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press start again on the LCP. The 3-way valve will be active, and the separator will start to discharge or filter fuel automatically with the following sequence mechanism:
a.	Check P244 (SV 15): open bowl; start discharge (10 seconds).
b.	Check P232 (SV 15): open bowl, discharge check, draining, and return increase speed (15 seconds)
c.	Check P257 (SV 16): closing bowl (15 seconds).
d.	Check P233 (SV 10): water seal (3 seconds).
e.	Check P258 (V1): A 3-way valve is active: BB starts to be filtered, and every 60 minutes, dirty BB and separated sludge will be removed by the separator by opening the bowl.
f.	Then P234 (SV 6) will be active to dump the sludge into the sludge/dirty oil tank (10 seconds).
8.	The system will run automatically, regulated by the PLC, and fill the daily BB tank.


B.	STOP SEPARATOR
1.	The sequence for turning off the separator is as follows:
a.	Check SV sludge is active (15 seconds)
b.	Stop the timer for 1737 seconds (at this time, the motor no longer rotates the separator, but the separator will continue to rotate until it stops).
2.	Close the Feed Pump suction valve by positioning the lever not in the direction of the pipe.
3.	Close valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank by positioning the valve to the right.
4.	Turn off the power supply on the LCP separator by positioning the knob toward off.
5.	Turn off the power supply at the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room). by positioning the knob at (0).
"}

{"description_id":"PROSEDUR PENGOPERASIAN SEPARATOR BAHAN BAKAR
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Nyalakan power supply pada MCC di Ruang DG (MCC Load Center DG Room) dengan memposisikan knob ke (1).
2.	Nyalakan power supply pada LCP separator dengan memposisikan knob ke on
3.	Buka valve M0134 (separator 1) atau Valve M0132 (separator 2) dari tanki.
a.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0134.
b.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0132.
4.	Buka klep hisap Feed Pump.
5.	Saat power supply sudah masuk, separator pada posisi standby, tekan tombol start (warna hijau) pada LCP dan akan muncul pertanyaan “to start feed pump press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (feed pump akan menyala selama ± 525 detik)
6.	Saat timer sudah 0 detik, akan muncul pertanyaan lagi “to start separation press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (motor akan mulai berputar dan mulai mengajak separator untuk berputar bersama secara perlahan melalui friction pad selama ± 239 detik).
7.	Kemudian akan muncul pertanyaan “ to start separation press start button “, lalu tekan start lagi pada LCP, 3 way valve akan aktif dan separator akan mulai mendischarge / menyaring bahan bakar scr otomatis dengan mekanisme urutan sebagai berikut : 
a.	Cek P244 (SV 15) : open bowl - start discharge ( 10 detik ).
b.	Cek P232 (SV 15) : open bowl – discharge check, draining & return increase speed ( 15 detik )
c.	Cek P257 (SV 16) : closing bowl (15 detik ).
d.	Cek P233 (SV 10) : water seal ( 3 detik ).
e.	Cek P258 (V1) : 3 way valve aktif – BB mulai disaring dan setiap 60 menit, BB kotor dan lumpur yg sudah terpisah akan dikeluarkan oleh separator dengan membuka bowl-nya.
f.	Lalu P234 (SV 6) akan aktif untuk membuang sludge ke sludge/dirty oil tank (10 detik).
8.	Sistem akan berjalan secara otomatis diatur oleh PLC dan mengisi ke tanki harian BB
","description_en":"FUEL SEPARATOR OPERATING PROCEDURES
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Turn on the power supply to the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room) by positioning the knob to (1).
2.	Turn on the power supply to the LCP separator by positioning the knob to
3.	Open valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank.
a.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0134.
b.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0132.
4.	Open the feed pump suction valve.
5.	When the power supply is in, the separator is in the standby position. Press the start button (green) on the LCP, and the question "To start the feed pump, press the start button" will appear. Then press the start button (the feed pump will turn on for ± 525 seconds).
6.	When the timer reaches 0 seconds, another question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press the start button (the motor will start rotating and start inviting the separator to rotate together slowly via the friction pad for ± 239 seconds).
7.	Then the question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press start again on the LCP. The 3-way valve will be active, and the separator will start to discharge or filter fuel automatically with the following sequence mechanism:
a.	Check P244 (SV 15): open bowl; start discharge (10 seconds).
b.	Check P232 (SV 15): open bowl, discharge check, draining, and return increase speed (15 seconds)
c.	Check P257 (SV 16): closing bowl (15 seconds).
d.	Check P233 (SV 10): water seal (3 seconds).
e.	Check P258 (V1): A 3-way valve is active: BB starts to be filtered, and every 60 minutes, dirty BB and separated sludge will be removed by the separator by opening the bowl.
f.	Then P234 (SV 6) will be active to dump the sludge into the sludge/dirty oil tank (10 seconds).
8.	The system will run automatically, regulated by the PLC, and fill the daily BB tank.


B.	STOP SEPARATOR
1.	The sequence for turning off the separator is as follows:
a.	Check SV sludge is active (15 seconds)
b.	Stop the timer for 1737 seconds (at this time, the motor no longer rotates the separator, but the separator will continue to rotate until it stops).
2.	Close the Feed Pump suction valve by positioning the lever not in the direction of the pipe.
3.	Close valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank by positioning the valve to the right.
4.	Turn off the power supply on the LCP separator by positioning the knob toward off.
5.	Turn off the power supply at the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room). by positioning the knob at (0).
"}

{"description_id":"PROSEDUR PENGOPERASIAN SEPARATOR BAHAN BAKAR
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Nyalakan power supply pada MCC di Ruang DG (MCC Load Center DG Room) dengan memposisikan knob ke (1).
2.	Nyalakan power supply pada LCP separator dengan memposisikan knob ke on
3.	Buka valve M0134 (separator 1) atau Valve M0132 (separator 2) dari tanki.
a.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0134.
b.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0132.
4.	Buka klep hisap Feed Pump.
5.	Saat power supply sudah masuk, separator pada posisi standby, tekan tombol start (warna hijau) pada LCP dan akan muncul pertanyaan “to start feed pump press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (feed pump akan menyala selama ± 525 detik)
6.	Saat timer sudah 0 detik, akan muncul pertanyaan lagi “to start separation press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (motor akan mulai berputar dan mulai mengajak separator untuk berputar bersama secara perlahan melalui friction pad selama ± 239 detik).
7.	Kemudian akan muncul pertanyaan “ to start separation press start button “, lalu tekan start lagi pada LCP, 3 way valve akan aktif dan separator akan mulai mendischarge / menyaring bahan bakar scr otomatis dengan mekanisme urutan sebagai berikut : 
a.	Cek P244 (SV 15) : open bowl - start discharge ( 10 detik ).
b.	Cek P232 (SV 15) : open bowl – discharge check, draining & return increase speed ( 15 detik )
c.	Cek P257 (SV 16) : closing bowl (15 detik ).
d.	Cek P233 (SV 10) : water seal ( 3 detik ).
e.	Cek P258 (V1) : 3 way valve aktif – BB mulai disaring dan setiap 60 menit, BB kotor dan lumpur yg sudah terpisah akan dikeluarkan oleh separator dengan membuka bowl-nya.
f.	Lalu P234 (SV 6) akan aktif untuk membuang sludge ke sludge/dirty oil tank (10 detik).
8.	Sistem akan berjalan secara otomatis diatur oleh PLC dan mengisi ke tanki harian BB
","description_en":"FUEL SEPARATOR OPERATING PROCEDURES
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Turn on the power supply to the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room) by positioning the knob to (1).
2.	Turn on the power supply to the LCP separator by positioning the knob to
3.	Open valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank.
a.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0134.
b.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0132.
4.	Open the feed pump suction valve.
5.	When the power supply is in, the separator is in the standby position. Press the start button (green) on the LCP, and the question "To start the feed pump, press the start button" will appear. Then press the start button (the feed pump will turn on for ± 525 seconds).
6.	When the timer reaches 0 seconds, another question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press the start button (the motor will start rotating and start inviting the separator to rotate together slowly via the friction pad for ± 239 seconds).
7.	Then the question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press start again on the LCP. The 3-way valve will be active, and the separator will start to discharge or filter fuel automatically with the following sequence mechanism:
a.	Check P244 (SV 15): open bowl; start discharge (10 seconds).
b.	Check P232 (SV 15): open bowl, discharge check, draining, and return increase speed (15 seconds)
c.	Check P257 (SV 16): closing bowl (15 seconds).
d.	Check P233 (SV 10): water seal (3 seconds).
e.	Check P258 (V1): A 3-way valve is active: BB starts to be filtered, and every 60 minutes, dirty BB and separated sludge will be removed by the separator by opening the bowl.
f.	Then P234 (SV 6) will be active to dump the sludge into the sludge/dirty oil tank (10 seconds).
8.	The system will run automatically, regulated by the PLC, and fill the daily BB tank.


B.	STOP SEPARATOR
1.	The sequence for turning off the separator is as follows:
a.	Check SV sludge is active (15 seconds)
b.	Stop the timer for 1737 seconds (at this time, the motor no longer rotates the separator, but the separator will continue to rotate until it stops).
2.	Close the Feed Pump suction valve by positioning the lever not in the direction of the pipe.
3.	Close valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank by positioning the valve to the right.
4.	Turn off the power supply on the LCP separator by positioning the knob toward off.
5.	Turn off the power supply at the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room). by positioning the knob at (0).
"}

c.	Check P257 (SV 16): closing bowl (15 seconds).
d.	Check P233 (SV 10): water seal (3 seconds).
e.	Check P258 (V1): A 3-way valve is active: BB starts to be filtered, and every 60 minutes, dirty BB and separated sludge will be removed by the separator by opening the bowl.
f.	Then P234 (SV 6) will be active to dump the sludge into the sludge/dirty oil tank (10 seconds).
8.	The system will run automatically, regulated by the PLC, and fill the daily BB tank.


B.	STOP SEPARATOR
1.	The sequence for turning off the separator is as follows:
a.	Check SV sludge is active (15 seconds)
b.	Stop the timer for 1737 seconds (at this time, the motor no longer rotates the separator, but the separator will continue to rotate until it stops).
2.	Close the Feed Pump suction valve by positioning the lever not in the direction of the pipe.
3.	Close valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank by positioning the valve to the right.
4.	Turn off the power supply on the LCP separator by positioning the knob toward off.
5.	Turn off the power supply at the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room). by positioning the knob at (0).
"}

description_json:
{"description_id":"PROSEDUR PENGOPERASIAN SEPARATOR BAHAN BAKAR
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Nyalakan power supply pada MCC di Ruang DG (MCC Load Center DG Room) dengan memposisikan knob ke (1).
2.	Nyalakan power supply pada LCP separator dengan memposisikan knob ke on
3.	Buka valve M0134 (separator 1) atau Valve M0132 (separator 2) dari tanki.
a.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0134.
b.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0132.
4.	Buka klep hisap Feed Pump.
5.	Saat power supply sudah masuk, separator pada posisi standby, tekan tombol start (warna hijau) pada LCP dan akan muncul pertanyaan “to start feed pump press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (feed pump akan menyala selama ± 525 detik)
6.	Saat timer sudah 0 detik, akan muncul pertanyaan lagi “to start separation press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (motor akan mulai berputar dan mulai mengajak separator untuk berputar bersama secara perlahan melalui friction pad selama ± 239 detik).
7.	Kemudian akan muncul pertanyaan “ to start separation press start button “, lalu tekan start lagi pada LCP, 3 way valve akan aktif dan separator akan mulai mendischarge / menyaring bahan bakar scr otomatis dengan mekanisme urutan sebagai berikut : 
a.	Cek P244 (SV 15) : open bowl - start discharge ( 10 detik ).
b.	Cek P232 (SV 15) : open bowl – discharge check, draining & return increase speed ( 15 detik )
c.	Cek P257 (SV 16) : closing bowl (15 detik ).
d.	Cek P233 (SV 10) : water seal ( 3 detik ).
e.	Cek P258 (V1) : 3 way valve aktif – BB mulai disaring dan setiap 60 menit, BB kotor dan lumpur yg sudah terpisah akan dikeluarkan oleh separator dengan membuka bowl-nya.
f.	Lalu P234 (SV 6) akan aktif untuk membuang sludge ke sludge/dirty oil tank (10 detik).
8.	Sistem akan berjalan secara otomatis diatur oleh PLC dan mengisi ke tanki harian BB
","description_en":"FUEL SEPARATOR OPERATING PROCEDURES
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Turn on the power supply to the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room) by positioning the knob to (1).
2.	Turn on the power supply to the LCP separator by positioning the knob to
3.	Open valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank.
a.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0134.
b.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0132.
4.	Open the feed pump suction valve.
5.	When the power supply is in, the separator is in the standby position. Press the start button (green) on the LCP, and the question "To start the feed pump, press the start button" will appear. Then press the start button (the feed pump will turn on for ± 525 seconds).
6.	When the timer reaches 0 seconds, another question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press the start button (the motor will start rotating and start inviting the separator to rotate together slowly via the friction pad for ± 239 seconds).
7.	Then the question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press start again on the LCP. The 3-way valve will be active, and the separator will start to discharge or filter fuel automatically with the following sequence mechanism:
a.	Check P244 (SV 15): open bowl; start discharge (10 seconds).
b.	Check P232 (SV 15): open bowl, discharge check, draining, and return increase speed (15 seconds)
c.	Check P257 (SV 16): closing bowl (15 seconds).
d.	Check P233 (SV 10): water seal (3 seconds).
e.	Check P258 (V1): A 3-way valve is active: BB starts to be filtered, and every 60 minutes, dirty BB and separated sludge will be removed by the separator by opening the bowl.
f.	Then P234 (SV 6) will be active to dump the sludge into the sludge/dirty oil tank (10 seconds).
8.	The system will run automatically, regulated by the PLC, and fill the daily BB tank.


B.	STOP SEPARATOR
1.	The sequence for turning off the separator is as follows:
a.	Check SV sludge is active (15 seconds)
b.	Stop the timer for 1737 seconds (at this time, the motor no longer rotates the separator, but the separator will continue to rotate until it stops).
2.	Close the Feed Pump suction valve by positioning the lever not in the direction of the pipe.
3.	Close valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank by positioning the valve to the right.
4.	Turn off the power supply on the LCP separator by positioning the knob toward off.
5.	Turn off the power supply at the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room). by positioning the knob at (0).
"}

{"description_id":"PROSEDUR PENGOPERASIAN SEPARATOR BAHAN BAKAR
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Nyalakan power supply pada MCC di Ruang DG (MCC Load Center DG Room) dengan memposisikan knob ke (1).
2.	Nyalakan power supply pada LCP separator dengan memposisikan knob ke on
3.	Buka valve M0134 (separator 1) atau Valve M0132 (separator 2) dari tanki.
a.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0134.
b.	Putar valve ke arah kiri untuk Valve M0132.
4.	Buka klep hisap Feed Pump.
5.	Saat power supply sudah masuk, separator pada posisi standby, tekan tombol start (warna hijau) pada LCP dan akan muncul pertanyaan “to start feed pump press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (feed pump akan menyala selama ± 525 detik)
6.	Saat timer sudah 0 detik, akan muncul pertanyaan lagi “to start separation press start button”, maka tekan tombol start (motor akan mulai berputar dan mulai mengajak separator untuk berputar bersama secara perlahan melalui friction pad selama ± 239 detik).
7.	Kemudian akan muncul pertanyaan “ to start separation press start button “, lalu tekan start lagi pada LCP, 3 way valve akan aktif dan separator akan mulai mendischarge / menyaring bahan bakar scr otomatis dengan mekanisme urutan sebagai berikut : 
a.	Cek P244 (SV 15) : open bowl - start discharge ( 10 detik ).
b.	Cek P232 (SV 15) : open bowl – discharge check, draining & return increase speed ( 15 detik )
c.	Cek P257 (SV 16) : closing bowl (15 detik ).
d.	Cek P233 (SV 10) : water seal ( 3 detik ).
e.	Cek P258 (V1) : 3 way valve aktif – BB mulai disaring dan setiap 60 menit, BB kotor dan lumpur yg sudah terpisah akan dikeluarkan oleh separator dengan membuka bowl-nya.
f.	Lalu P234 (SV 6) akan aktif untuk membuang sludge ke sludge/dirty oil tank (10 detik).
8.	Sistem akan berjalan secara otomatis diatur oleh PLC dan mengisi ke tanki harian BB
","description_en":"FUEL SEPARATOR OPERATING PROCEDURES
A.	START SEPARATOR
1.	Turn on the power supply to the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room) by positioning the knob to (1).
2.	Turn on the power supply to the LCP separator by positioning the knob to
3.	Open valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank.
a.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0134.
b.	Turn the valve to the left for valve M0132.
4.	Open the feed pump suction valve.
5.	When the power supply is in, the separator is in the standby position. Press the start button (green) on the LCP, and the question "To start the feed pump, press the start button" will appear. Then press the start button (the feed pump will turn on for ± 525 seconds).
6.	When the timer reaches 0 seconds, another question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press the start button (the motor will start rotating and start inviting the separator to rotate together slowly via the friction pad for ± 239 seconds).
7.	Then the question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press start again on the LCP. The 3-way valve will be active, and the separator will start to discharge or filter fuel automatically with the following sequence mechanism:
a.	Check P244 (SV 15): open bowl; start discharge (10 seconds).
b.	Check P232 (SV 15): open bowl, discharge check, draining, and return increase speed (15 seconds)
c.	Check P257 (SV 16): closing bowl (15 seconds).
d.	Check P233 (SV 10): water seal (3 seconds).
e.	Check P258 (V1): A 3-way valve is active: BB starts to be filtered, and every 60 minutes, dirty BB and separated sludge will be removed by the separator by opening the bowl.
f.	Then P234 (SV 6) will be active to dump the sludge into the sludge/dirty oil tank (10 seconds).
8.	The system will run automatically, regulated by the PLC, and fill the daily BB tank.


B.	STOP SEPARATOR
1.	The sequence for turning off the separator is as follows:
a.	Check SV sludge is active (15 seconds)
b.	Stop the timer for 1737 seconds (at this time, the motor no longer rotates the separator, but the separator will continue to rotate until it stops).
2.	Close the Feed Pump suction valve by positioning the lever not in the direction of the pipe.
3.	Close valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank by positioning the valve to the right.
4.	Turn off the power supply on the LCP separator by positioning the knob toward off.
5.	Turn off the power supply at the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room). by positioning the knob at (0).
"}

4.	Open the feed pump suction valve.

6.	When the timer reaches 0 seconds, another question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press the start button (the motor will start rotating and start inviting the separator to rotate together slowly via the friction pad for ± 239 seconds).
7.	Then the question will appear: "To start separation, press the start button,"  then press start again on the LCP. The 3-way valve will be active, and the separator will start to discharge or filter fuel automatically with the following sequence mechanism:
a.	Check P244 (SV 15): open bowl; start discharge (10 seconds).
b.	Check P232 (SV 15): open bowl, discharge check, draining, and return increase speed (15 seconds)
c.	Check P257 (SV 16): closing bowl (15 seconds).
d.	Check P233 (SV 10): water seal (3 seconds).
e.	Check P258 (V1): A 3-way valve is active: BB starts to be filtered, and every 60 minutes, dirty BB and separated sludge will be removed by the separator by opening the bowl.
f.	Then P234 (SV 6) will be active to dump the sludge into the sludge/dirty oil tank (10 seconds).
8.	The system will run automatically, regulated by the PLC, and fill the daily BB tank.


B.	STOP SEPARATOR
1.	The sequence for turning off the separator is as follows:
a.	Check SV sludge is active (15 seconds)
b.	Stop the timer for 1737 seconds (at this time, the motor no longer rotates the separator, but the separator will continue to rotate until it stops).
2.	Close the Feed Pump suction valve by positioning the lever not in the direction of the pipe.
3.	Close valve M0134 (separator 1) or valve M0132 (separator 2) from the tank by positioning the valve to the right.
4.	Turn off the power supply on the LCP separator by positioning the knob toward off.
5.	Turn off the power supply at the MCC in the DG Room (MCC Load Center DG Room). by positioning the knob at (0).
"}
